  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most countries. It typically falls under criminal legislation and is prosecuted as a serious financial crime. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or bank accounts to make it appear legal. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations that criminalize such activities, with potential penalties including substantial fines and imprisonment.",
